The paper deals with distributed data structures and algorithms for computing Top-k and k-Select queries, which are fundamental problems in data management and analysis. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also focuses on communication efficiency, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the use of probability and information theory in the analysis of the algorithms suggests that it may belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
